8 AS INTRODUCED
9 A Concurrent Resolution honoring the 50th anniversary
of the Fall of Saigon and end of the Vietnam War;
10 recognizing the subsequent growth of the Vietnamese
American community, culture, and economic impact in
11 Oklahoma; and celebrating those who fought for the
freedom of Vietnam and Vietnamese American citizens.
12
13
14 WHEREAS, April 30, 2025, marks the 50th anniversary of the Fall
15 of Saigon, a pivotal moment in world history which marked the end of
16 the Vietnam War and led to mass displacement of millions of
17 Vietnamese refugees; and
18 WHEREAS, many Vietnamese families fled their homeland in search
19 of freedom, safety, and opportunity, enduring perilous journeys and
20 resettling in countries around the world, including the United
21 States; and
22 WHEREAS, the State of Oklahoma became home to a vibrant
23 Vietnamese American community that has enriched the state's
