11 Year) and the preservation of Vietnamese heritage have strengthened
12 Oklahoma's multicultural identity and promoted cross-cultural
13 understanding; and
14 WHEREAS, this 50th anniversary provides an opportunity for all
15 Oklahomans to reflect on the tragic costs of war, the power of
16 perseverance, and the enduring values of freedom and democracy; and
17 WHEREAS, in honoring and recognizing our Vietnamese American
18 Community, the State of Oklahoma continues to recognize the South
19 Republic Heritage flag (yellow flag with three red stripes) as the
20 official flag to honor those who have fought for the freedom of
21 Vietnam and our fellow Vietnamese American citizens of the State of
22 Oklahoma; and
